Overview

Ask Chatbot is an AI-powered chatbot application built using Streamlit and LangChain. It leverages FAISS vector store for document retrieval and Mistral-7B model from Hugging Face to provide intelligent responses based on provided context.

Features

Utilizes Hugging Face embeddings for vector storage and retrieval

FAISS for efficient similarity search

Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) using LangChain

Streamlit UI for user-friendly interactions

Installation

Prerequisites

Ensure you have Python 3.8+ installed along with the required dependencies.

Setup

Create and activate a virtual environment (optional but recommended):

python -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate  # On macOS/Linux
venv\Scripts\activate  # On Windows

Install dependencies:

pip install -r requirements.txt

Create a .env file and add necessary environment variables if required.

Running the Application

Start the Streamlit application using:

streamlit run app.py

Folder Structure

<repo-name>/
│── vectorstore/          # FAISS vector store directory
│── app.py               # Main chatbot application
│── requirements.txt     # Required dependencies
│── .env                 # Environment variables (optional)
└── README.md            # Project documentation

Usage

Run the application.

Enter your query in the chatbot interface.

The chatbot will retrieve relevant information and respond accordingly.

Technologies Used

Python

Streamlit

LangChain

FAISS

Hugging Face Models

